[SN]TITLE[SN]
Brechin Bridge closed after second collision

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
The Brechin Bridge has been closed after being damaged by a vehicle for the second time this year.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Angus Council said it was alerted by police after a road traffic collision on the bridge at about 23:30 on Wednesday.
The council said a bridge engineer would assess the latest damage and the repair work required.
The parapet of the bridge was previously damaged by a vehicle in February.
Diversions have been put in place from Kinnell crossroads (A933) via the A934 to Montrose and back along the A935.
